summaries.short: When the Nuclear Family tracks them down, Dick, Kory, Rachel and Gar decide to stop running and work together, and the team that will be known as "The Titans" is formed.
summaries.full: When the Nuclear Family tracks them down, Dick, Kory, Rachel and Gar decide to stop running and work together, and the team that will be known as "The Titans" is formed.

summaries.short: Before he can reunite with the Titans, Dick reluctantly teams with Jason Todd, the new Robin, to catch a serial killer targeting performers from Dick's surrogate circus family from when he was a member of the Flying Graysons.
summaries.full: Before he can reunite with the Titans, Dick reluctantly teams with Jason Todd, the new Robin, to catch a serial killer targeting performers from Dick's surrogate circus family from when he was a member of the Flying Graysons.

summaries.short: Gar brings Rachel home to his family, a group of misfit medical experiments who will become known as the Doom Patrol, including Robotman, Negative Man and Elastigirl.
summaries.full: Gar brings Rachel home to his family, a group of misfit medical experiments who will become known as the Doom Patrol, including Robotman, Negative Man and Elastigirl.

summaries.short: The Titans set out to rescue Rachel's birth mother from a mysterious psychiatric facility.
summaries.full: When the Messenger reveals that Rachel's birth mother is alive and being held captive by the Organization in a mysterious psychiatric facility, Rachel is determined to rescue her; the Titans are faced with their deepest vulnerabilities and fears.

summaries.short: Rachel and Kory travel to the convent where Rachel was raised, while Dick compares his own orphan experience to Rachel's; Rachel befriends Gar Logan.
summaries.full: Rachel and Kory travel to the convent where Rachel was raised, while Dick compares his own orphan experience to Rachel's; Rachel befriends Gar Logan.

summaries.short: As the Titans go their separate ways, Dick turns to old friend Donna Troy for answers.
summaries.full: As the Titans disband to go their separate ways, Dick decides to turn to old friend and investigative journalist Donna Troy, aka Wonder Girl, for answers; he realizes past events have taken more of a psychological toll than he previously thought.

summaries.short: In search of a safe haven for Rachel, Dick arrives on the doorstep of vigilante heroes Hawk and Dove.
summaries.full: In search of a safe haven for Rachel, Dick arrives on the doorstep of vigilante heroes Hawk and Dove.
